inci_des_1: Bala pools security incident -On 22 of May 2011 three unknown armed men wearing SPLA type uniforms killed two people at the Bala pools construction site of the Badingilo Park headquarters. A MWCT wildlife ranger and a Ugandan Terrain construction company employee were shot and killed while walking to the construction site. A South Sudan Police investigation along with WCS and MWCT enquiries confirmed this report. It was suspected that the perpetrators were from roaming armed tribal groups, which are known to raid and rob people in that sector. Following the incident the construction company suspended its operations for two weeks, and the MWCT deployed additional security forces to the site. Construction activities were resumed and the initial works completed in early July.

inci_des_1: August 23, 2013. A field crew member was injured while working as a guide for the dump trucks transporting soil from the SA into the IPTD. The crew members right thumb was caught between the tailgate and the bed of the dump truck while the tailgate was closing, pinching the thumb and causing it to bleed. The injury was cleaned and dressed, and the crew member was taken to the local hospital for an x-ray to assure that no internal injuries had occurred. The crew member was back to work with no loss work time reported. Prior to the injury incident, there were 137 injury-free working days or 75,782 injury-free working hours since the last injury reported on April 7, 2013.
inci_des_2: April 7, 2013.The Tt Health and Safety Officer accidentally injured his foreleg while pushing motorcycle out of the office. This injury required medical attendance and thus became reportable. Prior to that, there have been 174 injury/incident-free working days.
env_inc_des_1: On Friday of August 17, 2013, a dump truck was transporting a load of excavated soil from the storage area through the ramp into the IPTD when the tailgate of the truck opened. Approximately 3 cubic meters of soil spilled out onto the ramp. The H&S crews and support team immediately closed the ramp and cleaned up the affected area.
env_inc_des_2: In the afternoon of July 9, a severe thunderstorm came through Danang. Turbid stormwater flowed out from the IPTD structure through the southern entrance of the pile, through the concrete blocks and onto the gravel at the south end of the structure. Control measures (rock check dam and silt fencing) were instituted immediately after the spill was identified. Crews removed gravel from the areas where the spill occurred on July 10, 2013 and placed it into the pile for treatment. Tetra Tech removed surficial fill in areas affected by the spill and created a spill report. A 30-point composite sample was collected from the area affected by the spill and contained 124 ppt Total Dioxin TEQ. This result is below our the cleanup level of 150 ppt Total Dioxin TEQ for sediment and indicates that the contaminated material was effectively removed from the area.
